description: Gets the aggregated profile of a profiling group for a specified time range. Amazon CodeGuru Profiler collects posted agent profiles for a profiling group into aggregated profiles.

parameters.name: accept
parameters.description:
The format of the returned profiling data. The format maps to the Accept and Content-Type headers of the HTTP request. You can specify one of the following: or the default . ``

  • application/json -- standard JSON format

  • application/x-amzn-ion -- the Amazon Ion data format. For more information, see Amazon Ion.

``

parameters.name: endTime
parameters.description: The end time of the requested profile. Specify using the ISO 8601 format. For example, 2020-06-01T13:15:02.001Z represents 1 millisecond past June 1, 2020 1:15:02 PM UTC. If you specify endTime, then you must also specify period or startTime, but not both.

parameters.name: period
parameters.description:
Used with startTime or endTime to specify the time range for the returned aggregated profile. Specify using the ISO 8601 format. For example, P1DT1H1M1S. ``

To get the latest aggregated profile, specify only period.

``

parameters.name: profilingGroupName
parameters.description: The name of the profiling group to get.

parameters.name: startTime
parameters.description:
The start time of the profile to get. Specify using the ISO 8601 format. For example, 2020-06-01T13:15:02.001Z represents 1 millisecond past June 1, 2020 1:15:02 PM UTC. ``

If you specify startTime, then you must also specify period or endTime, but not both.

``

nested_items.name: contentEncoding
nested_items.description: The content encoding of the profile.

nested_items.name: contentType
nested_items.description: The content type of the profile in the payload. It is either application/json or the default application/x-amzn-ion.
